by clay » Sun 11.29.2009 6:16 pm Gosh Phreadom, is there anything you don't have a strong opinion on? My original Xbox did get the Red Circle of Death, but they exchanged it promptly and I haven't had a problem since. In my experience Microsoft has been very good. I do love my Wii, but I just haven't played it in months. If I had boatloads of money and no mortgage, I would get a PS3 in a heartbeat.EDIT: I just wanted to mention a cool feature on the Xbox I didn't know about. Today was Makoto's 4th birthday party and I wanted the TV to display a slideshow of his baby pictures. Just on a whim I searched the Xbox for USB ports, found two in the front, and stuck a USB thumb drive in and seconds later, I had my slideshow. I knew I could connect to my computer through Windows Media Center, but I hadn't had much luck with getting the Media Center to work right.
